1
00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:03,050
 Previously on Lucifer...

2
00:00:03,050 --> 00:00:05,037
Ooh! How's your ex,
Detective Douche?

3
00:00:05,037 --> 00:00:07,054
Is this the fight that
you want to pick?

4
00:00:07,054 --> 00:00:08,067
You stuck your neck
out on Palmetto.

5
00:00:08,068 --> 00:00:11,044
Look where
that got you.
Okay.

6
00:00:11,045 --> 00:00:13,055
Chloe, you are stabbing hard

7
00:00:13,055 --> 00:00:15,071
 at something
 that's just not there.

8
00:00:15,072 --> 00:00:17,015
CHLOE:
 There's got to be
 an explanation

9
00:00:17,015 --> 00:00:18,025
 for what I saw, Dan.

10
00:00:18,025 --> 00:00:19,059
There has to be!

11
00:00:19,059 --> 00:00:20,039
DAN:
 Chloe, this could mean

12
00:00:20,039 --> 00:00:21,068
 a lot of things.

13
00:00:21,068 --> 00:00:22,097
CHLOE:
 It means a cop knew

14
00:00:22,097 --> 00:00:24,026
 this secret passageway
 existed, Dan.

15
00:00:24,026 --> 00:00:25,072
What is it?
A 999 key.

16
00:00:25,073 --> 00:00:28,039
LAPD issued.
I was right.

17
00:00:28,040 --> 00:00:30,060
AMENADIEL:
 It's my duty to return
 the wings where they belong.

18
00:00:30,060 --> 00:00:31,076
 Doesn't part of you long

19
00:00:31,077 --> 00:00:33,013
to assume your form?

20
00:00:33,013 --> 00:00:34,080
Not exactly.

21
00:00:36,090 --> 00:00:38,040
MAZE: I want
 what's best for Lucifer.

22
00:00:38,041 --> 00:00:39,079
AMENADIEL:
 Then give me something

23
00:00:39,079 --> 00:00:41,017
that I can use against Lucifer,
 and I'll make

24
00:00:41,018 --> 00:00:42,027
sure you're both back
where you belong.

25
00:00:42,028 --> 00:00:43,054
That's the problem.

26
00:00:43,054 --> 00:00:45,018
 He doesn't
 confide in me anymore.

27
00:00:45,018 --> 00:00:47,035
 But there is someone
 he does talk to.

28
00:00:47,035 --> 00:00:48,028
A doctor.

29
00:00:48,028 --> 00:00:49,058
Hello there, neighbor.

30
00:00:49,058 --> 00:00:51,082
I actually need someone
to confide in

31
00:00:51,082 --> 00:00:52,082
 about a patient.

32
00:00:52,082 --> 00:00:53,079
 And, hey, listen,

33
00:00:53,079 --> 00:00:54,075
 if you have any patients

34
00:00:54,076 --> 00:00:56,042
 you need to talk about...

35
00:00:57,086 --> 00:01:00,089
LINDA: You have no idea.

36
00:01:00,090 --> 00:01:04,086
(rock intro
to "Rebel Rebel" playing)

37
00:01:07,090 --> 00:01:10,057
♪ ♪

38
00:01:12,091 --> 00:01:16,048
♪ Got your mother in a whirl ♪

39
00:01:16,048 --> 00:01:20,035
♪ She's not sure if
you're a boy or a girl ♪

40
00:01:20,035 --> 00:01:23,038
♪ Hey, babe,
your hair's all right... ♪

41
00:01:23,038 --> 00:01:24,072
Lovely. Thanks, girls.
(chuckles)

42
00:01:24,072 --> 00:01:26,072
♪ Hey, babe,
let's go out tonight... ♪

43
00:01:26,072 --> 00:01:27,089
Ooh!

44
00:01:27,089 --> 00:01:29,072
♪ You like me,
and I like it all... ♪

45
00:01:29,072 --> 00:01:31,036
We'll have to try that later.

46
00:01:31,036 --> 00:01:34,073
♪ We like dancing
and we look divine... ♪

47
00:01:34,073 --> 00:01:36,020
Brian! Cheers!

48
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:39,057
♪ You love bands
when they're playing hard ♪

49
00:01:39,057 --> 00:01:42,094
♪ You want more
and you want it fast ♪

50
00:01:42,094 --> 00:01:44,087
♪ They put you down... ♪

51
00:01:44,087 --> 00:01:47,047
Maze! You haven't
wished me happy birthday.

52
00:01:47,047 --> 00:01:48,094
The Devil doesn't
have a birthday.

53
00:01:48,094 --> 00:01:50,028
Well, I do now.

54
00:01:50,028 --> 00:01:51,028
I burned my wings.

55
00:01:51,028 --> 00:01:52,068
I feel reborn.

56
00:01:52,068 --> 00:01:54,035
It's my re-birthday party.

57
00:01:54,035 --> 00:01:55,035
(chuckles)

58
00:01:55,035 --> 00:01:56,078
Reborn? As who?

59
00:01:56,078 --> 00:01:58,062
Whoever the hell
I want to be.

60
00:01:58,062 --> 00:02:00,069
It's exciting, isn't it?

61
00:02:00,069 --> 00:02:01,099
(inhales)

62
00:02:01,099 --> 00:02:03,076
♪ Hot tramp, I love you so ♪

63
00:02:03,076 --> 00:02:05,076
Ha-ha.

64
00:02:08,043 --> 00:02:09,053
To new beginnings.

65
00:02:09,053 --> 00:02:11,023
Happy birthday to me.

66
00:02:11,023 --> 00:02:12,093
Oh, how sweet.

67
00:02:12,093 --> 00:02:14,037
She brought a date.

68
00:02:14,037 --> 00:02:17,050
♪ Got your mother in a whirl ♪

69
00:02:17,050 --> 00:02:21,054
♪ 'Cause she's not sure
if you're a boy or a girl ♪

70
00:02:21,054 --> 00:02:24,091
♪ Hey, babe,
your hair's all right ♪

71
00:02:24,091 --> 00:02:26,065
♪ Hey, babe, let's... ♪

72
00:02:26,065 --> 00:02:28,038
(laughing): You said
"drinks with a few friends."

73
00:02:28,038 --> 00:02:29,082
Well, you know,
things got out of hand.

74
00:02:29,082 --> 00:02:31,078
Just the way I like it.
(chuckles)

75
00:02:31,079 --> 00:02:33,052
We brought you a birthday gift.

76
00:02:33,052 --> 00:02:34,069
Is that the royal "we"?

77
00:02:34,069 --> 00:02:36,066
Whiskey with
a pickle juice chaser.

78
00:02:36,066 --> 00:02:38,096
It's our station's
birthday tradition.

79
00:02:38,096 --> 00:02:40,063
Lovely! How can I refuse?

80
00:02:40,063 --> 00:02:41,079
Can I refuse?

81
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:42,093
DAN:
Of course you can.

82
00:02:42,093 --> 00:02:45,040
And we'll always
think less of you.

83
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:47,080
Here's to another
trip around the sun.

84
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:49,027
Cheers.

85
00:02:49,027 --> 00:02:51,080
♪ You put them on ♪

86
00:02:51,081 --> 00:02:55,041
♪ Rebel Rebel,
you've torn your dress ♪

87
00:02:55,041 --> 00:02:57,031
Ah! Ooh!

88
00:02:57,031 --> 00:02:58,068
It's not bad, is it?

89
00:02:58,068 --> 00:02:59,068
Briny!

90
00:02:59,068 --> 00:03:00,088
Let's find Maze.

91
00:03:00,088 --> 00:03:02,071
She needs to try this
bizarre concoction.

92
00:03:02,072 --> 00:03:04,065
She loves a salty aftertaste.

93
00:03:04,065 --> 00:03:05,088
No. We're just stopping by.

94
00:03:05,089 --> 00:03:07,005
We have a department
thing to go to.

95
00:03:07,005 --> 00:03:08,099
Some of us work
for a living.

96
00:03:08,099 --> 00:03:10,056
Well, that's your
bad luck, isn't it?

97
00:03:10,056 --> 00:03:12,042
Come on, the party's
barely started.

98
00:03:13,036 --> 00:03:15,083
Happy birthday, Lucifer.

99
00:03:21,097 --> 00:03:23,097
("Rebel Rebel" ends)

100
00:03:23,097 --> 00:03:26,084
♪ ♪

101
00:03:26,084 --> 00:03:29,007
(indistinct conversations,
rock music playing)

102
00:03:32,085 --> 00:03:34,071
You sure you want
to be here?

103
00:03:34,072 --> 00:03:36,048
We can't be the only ones

104
00:03:36,048 --> 00:03:38,005
missing Malcolm's
welcome back party.

105
00:03:38,005 --> 00:03:39,072
If we want to find
a dirty cop,

106
00:03:39,072 --> 00:03:41,005
we got to look
like team players.

107
00:03:41,006 --> 00:03:42,032
MAN:
Chloe Decker!

108
00:03:46,006 --> 00:03:47,046
Here we go.

109
00:03:47,046 --> 00:03:48,086
♪ Call me up
on your little black phone ♪

110
00:03:48,086 --> 00:03:52,073
♪ Look for a big surprise... ♪

111
00:03:52,073 --> 00:03:54,047
You and I need to talk.

112
00:03:54,047 --> 00:03:57,000
Sure, Malcolm.

113
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,071
♪ Every time you
come 'round... ♪

114
00:03:59,071 --> 00:04:01,047
You back with this guy?

115
00:04:01,048 --> 00:04:02,081
Hmm?

116
00:04:02,081 --> 00:04:04,061
How-how, how long was I out?

117
00:04:04,061 --> 00:04:06,041
What, you get the sense
knocked out of you, Decker?

118
00:04:06,041 --> 00:04:08,005
We're just, we're just...
You know, we have...

119
00:04:08,005 --> 00:04:09,041
(laughing):
Just relax, guys.

120
00:04:09,042 --> 00:04:10,092
I'm just... just
giving you a hard time.

121
00:04:10,092 --> 00:04:12,075
(Malcolm laughing)

122
00:04:12,075 --> 00:04:14,075
Oh. Wow.
You finally got
your sense of humor back, huh?

123
00:04:14,076 --> 00:04:16,076
Yeah, he's healing fast.

124
00:04:16,076 --> 00:04:18,009
Doc said he should be able

125
00:04:18,009 --> 00:04:20,036
to get rid of this chair
in a couple days.

126
00:04:20,036 --> 00:04:22,076
(grunting): You tired of
pushing me around, Paolucci?

127
00:04:22,076 --> 00:04:25,000
(Paolucci chuckles)

128
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,093
PAOLUCCI:
Look at that, huh?

129
00:04:26,093 --> 00:04:29,007
The partner who
will not die.

130
00:04:29,007 --> 00:04:30,064
(Malcolm laughs)

131
00:04:30,064 --> 00:04:32,007
PAOLUCCI:
Guess Heaven didn't want him

132
00:04:32,007 --> 00:04:33,041
and Hell couldn't keep him.

133
00:04:33,041 --> 00:04:35,001
(both chuckling)

134
00:04:35,001 --> 00:04:36,058
You got no idea.

135
00:04:36,058 --> 00:04:37,098
♪ Devil in your eyes. ♪

136
00:04:40,051 --> 00:04:42,011
So I, I may have been...

137
00:04:42,012 --> 00:04:43,095
(groans)

138
00:04:43,095 --> 00:04:45,078
...out of line last time
I was here.

139
00:04:47,089 --> 00:04:49,039
But I did send flowers.

140
00:04:49,039 --> 00:04:51,056
And chocolates.

141
00:04:51,056 --> 00:04:54,006
And now myself, so,
save the best gift till last.

142
00:04:54,006 --> 00:04:55,006
(nervous chuckle)

143
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:59,053
Not enough? No?

144
00:04:59,053 --> 00:05:01,000
You can invite a friend.
(nervous laugh)

145
00:05:03,050 --> 00:05:05,070
Why did you think I'd be mad?

146
00:05:07,098 --> 00:05:10,071
Was it because of this?

147
00:05:10,071 --> 00:05:12,061
(nervous laugh)

148
00:05:12,061 --> 00:05:13,095
I've found women, generally,

149
00:05:13,095 --> 00:05:16,062
don't like a man punching
holes in things, yes.

150
00:05:18,009 --> 00:05:20,099
Lucifer, our last session
was a breakthrough.

151
00:05:20,099 --> 00:05:23,072
It was?

152
00:05:23,072 --> 00:05:26,009
You're finally getting
in touch with your emotions.

153
00:05:26,009 --> 00:05:27,069
Letting your barriers down.

154
00:05:27,069 --> 00:05:29,009
You see, that's part
of the problem.

155
00:05:29,010 --> 00:05:31,013
I'd like them back up,
thank you.

156
00:05:31,013 --> 00:05:32,013
Why?

157
00:05:32,013 --> 00:05:34,053
Well, because
these emotions

158
00:05:34,053 --> 00:05:36,094
are... bloody inconvenient,
that's why.

159
00:05:38,057 --> 00:05:39,091
What's bothering you right now?

160
00:05:40,094 --> 00:05:42,052
(sighs):
Well...

161
00:05:42,053 --> 00:05:44,011
right now I'm experiencing
a very odd feeling.

162
00:05:44,011 --> 00:05:45,091
It's-it's like a...

163
00:05:45,091 --> 00:05:47,088
it's like a fat man
sitting on my chest.

164
00:05:47,088 --> 00:05:50,085
But not in a fun way.

165
00:05:50,085 --> 00:05:52,095
And when is that happening?

166
00:05:54,002 --> 00:05:55,002
Well, um...

167
00:05:55,002 --> 00:05:56,015
When you're with Chloe?

168
00:05:56,016 --> 00:05:58,007
Yes.

169
00:05:58,007 --> 00:05:59,099
Well, actually, lately,
when she's been with Dan.

170
00:05:59,099 --> 00:06:01,023
Her ex.

171
00:06:01,023 --> 00:06:03,050
Well, sort of. Uh...

172
00:06:03,050 --> 00:06:05,020
I don't know what
she sees in that oaf.

173
00:06:05,020 --> 00:06:06,023
Lucifer...

174
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:08,090
...you're jealous.

175
00:06:08,090 --> 00:06:12,007
The Devil doesn't get jealous.

176
00:06:12,007 --> 00:06:14,001
I'm the one who inspires
passion in others.

177
00:06:14,001 --> 00:06:15,004
(chuckling):
I mean...

178
00:06:15,004 --> 00:06:16,048
you know that.

179
00:06:16,048 --> 00:06:17,098
Mm, don't I ever.

180
00:06:17,098 --> 00:06:18,098
Thank you.

181
00:06:18,098 --> 00:06:20,091
That's the
appropriate response.

182
00:06:20,091 --> 00:06:21,091
(inhales)

183
00:06:23,098 --> 00:06:25,058
Hold on, maybe it's not me.

184
00:06:25,059 --> 00:06:28,049
Maybe it's her.
(gasps quietly)

185
00:06:28,049 --> 00:06:30,002
You could fix the detective.

186
00:06:30,002 --> 00:06:32,049
How would I do that?

187
00:06:32,049 --> 00:06:34,089
Well, heal her douche
fixation, obviously.

188
00:06:34,090 --> 00:06:36,076
Then she stays
away from her ex.

189
00:06:36,076 --> 00:06:38,026
Then I get my partner back.

190
00:06:38,027 --> 00:06:40,020
That's not how therapy works.

191
00:06:40,020 --> 00:06:41,098
(scoffs)

192
00:06:41,098 --> 00:06:43,077
We deal with your issues.

193
00:06:43,077 --> 00:06:45,050
Not someone else's.

194
00:06:45,051 --> 00:06:46,054
(scoffs)

195
00:06:48,091 --> 00:06:51,088
♪ ♪

196
00:06:55,025 --> 00:06:57,028
(low, indistinct conversation)

197
00:07:04,069 --> 00:07:07,079
Oh, dear! Someone's
session went poorly.

198
00:07:07,079 --> 00:07:09,066
Mm. Thanks for gracing us
with your presence.

199
00:07:09,066 --> 00:07:11,013
Yes, I had
a previous engagement.

200
00:07:11,013 --> 00:07:13,070
Therapy twice in one day.
So L.A. of me.

201
00:07:13,070 --> 00:07:16,007
Dr. Bernie Shaw.
Killed last night.

202
00:07:16,007 --> 00:07:17,007
No forced entry.

203
00:07:17,007 --> 00:07:18,064
Killer most likely
knew the vic.

204
00:07:18,064 --> 00:07:20,024
The weapon was improvised.

205
00:07:20,024 --> 00:07:21,071
Seems like a crime of passion.

206
00:07:21,071 --> 00:07:23,081
Right. Yeah.

207
00:07:23,081 --> 00:07:26,081
Have you ever
seen a therapist?

208
00:07:26,081 --> 00:07:29,095
You know, for your pent-up
anger and your trust issues.

209
00:07:29,095 --> 00:07:31,068
And your attraction
to very dull men.

210
00:07:31,069 --> 00:07:34,009
Let's just focus
on the case, shall we?

211
00:07:34,009 --> 00:07:35,072
Well, I will,
once it's interesting.

212
00:07:35,072 --> 00:07:38,006
Oh! Hello.

213
00:07:38,006 --> 00:07:40,056
It's interesting--
"The Cheater Therapist."

214
00:07:40,056 --> 00:07:42,056
Yeah, he encouraged couples to
cheat to save their marriages.

215
00:07:42,056 --> 00:07:44,070
You can imagine how many
people want to kill him.

216
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:46,070
I can't, actually.
Sounds like a great idea.

217
00:07:46,070 --> 00:07:48,083
You don't save a marriage
by sleeping with other people.

218
00:07:48,084 --> 00:07:50,010
It can't hurt to try.

219
00:07:51,010 --> 00:07:52,060
Pretty sure it can.

220
00:07:52,061 --> 00:07:54,057
(chuckles)

221
00:07:54,058 --> 00:07:56,024
(camera clicking)

222
00:07:58,011 --> 00:08:00,058
That's the wife Alexandra.

223
00:08:00,058 --> 00:08:02,011
She was out of town
and just got back

224
00:08:02,012 --> 00:08:03,025
to find her husband dead.

225
00:08:03,025 --> 00:08:04,075
Poor woman.

226
00:08:04,075 --> 00:08:06,079
Excuse me!

227
00:08:06,079 --> 00:08:08,022
Your husband was
the Cheater Therapist.

228
00:08:08,022 --> 00:08:10,012
Hey, I'm not sure
who you are,

229
00:08:10,012 --> 00:08:12,006
but this is not the time
for judgment.

230
00:08:12,006 --> 00:08:13,073
What? No judgment here,
Tissue Lad.

231
00:08:13,073 --> 00:08:16,013
I think her husband's
work was bang on!

232
00:08:16,013 --> 00:08:17,026
I'm Detective Decker.

233
00:08:17,026 --> 00:08:19,003
This is my associate,
Mr. Morningstar.

234
00:08:19,003 --> 00:08:19,086
Yeah, yeah.

235
00:08:19,087 --> 00:08:21,027
Jonathan Medina.

236
00:08:21,027 --> 00:08:22,073
Colleague of Dr. Shaw's.

237
00:08:22,074 --> 00:08:25,014
Desire shouldn't be
contained-- it's unnatural.

238
00:08:25,014 --> 00:08:27,064
Your husband
recognized that.

239
00:08:27,064 --> 00:08:30,088
Bernie, he-he just
wanted to help people.

240
00:08:30,088 --> 00:08:32,074
He dedicated his
life to others.

241
00:08:33,075 --> 00:08:35,011
Who would do this?

242
00:08:35,012 --> 00:08:36,085
We'll find out, Mrs. Shaw.

243
00:08:37,092 --> 00:08:38,092
Hmm?

244
00:08:43,019 --> 00:08:44,044
(speaking gently)

245
00:08:44,044 --> 00:08:45,069
Every one of her husband's
patients is a suspect.

246
00:08:45,069 --> 00:08:47,079
Oh! Does that mean we get
to dive into patient files?

247
00:08:47,079 --> 00:08:50,000
Read the deepest,
darkest secrets

248
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,033
of L.A.'s most unfaithful?

249
00:08:51,033 --> 00:08:53,010
No, we can't look at them
without a psychologist

250
00:08:53,010 --> 00:08:55,003
to protect patient
confidentiality.

251
00:08:55,004 --> 00:08:56,094
Perfect!
I have just the psychologist!

252
00:08:56,094 --> 00:09:00,037
Dr. Linda Martin, from our
first investigation together.

253
00:09:00,037 --> 00:09:01,081
The one that wanted
to jump your bones?

254
00:09:01,081 --> 00:09:02,087
Yeah.
No. Not happening.

255
00:09:02,088 --> 00:09:04,001
No, I really think
she'd bring some

256
00:09:04,001 --> 00:09:05,038
impressive insight
into the issues

257
00:09:05,038 --> 00:09:06,068
that you're dealing with.

258
00:09:06,068 --> 00:09:08,008
Uh, in the case.

259
00:09:08,008 --> 00:09:09,081
I really don't.
Plus, it's out of our hands.

260
00:09:09,082 --> 00:09:12,008
Court-appointed.
A judge needs to sign off.

261
00:09:17,009 --> 00:09:19,009
♪ ♪

262
00:09:25,017 --> 00:09:27,093
Wonderful! Now...

263
00:09:27,093 --> 00:09:29,083
I see you brought
your gavel, like I asked.

264
00:09:31,024 --> 00:09:33,067
(Lucifer sighs passionately)

265
00:09:33,067 --> 00:09:34,067
(Michelle laughs)

