00:28:51,036 --> 00:28:53,033
they've decided
that I'm jealous.

801
00:28:54,053 --> 00:28:56,083
So... what do you think?

802
00:28:56,084 --> 00:28:57,087
Huh?

803
00:28:57,087 --> 00:28:58,057
Yes.

804
00:28:58,057 --> 00:29:00,010
So, wait, you're the Devil?

805
00:29:00,011 --> 00:29:01,031
Yes, yes.

806
00:29:01,031 --> 00:29:03,034
Please keep up.
Anyone. You.

807
00:29:03,034 --> 00:29:05,014
When you say you, uh,
burned your wings,

808
00:29:05,014 --> 00:29:06,059
was that a metaphor...?

809
00:29:06,060 --> 00:29:08,005
Not focusing
on the right details!

810
00:29:08,005 --> 00:29:09,098
Uh, yeah.

811
00:29:09,098 --> 00:29:11,032
She was gonna throw poop at me?

812
00:29:11,032 --> 00:29:13,002
God, this isn't
about you, Tiffany.

813
00:29:13,002 --> 00:29:14,015
(laughs):
All right?

814
00:29:14,015 --> 00:29:16,022
Huh, no wonder
you're all in therapy.

815
00:29:16,022 --> 00:29:19,029
All right, this is supposed
to be a grief therapy session

816
00:29:19,029 --> 00:29:21,071
for the patients
of Dr. Shaw.

817
00:29:21,071 --> 00:29:24,013
And everyone here has
a terrible loss to deal with.

818
00:29:24,013 --> 00:29:25,078
What, and I don't?

819
00:29:25,078 --> 00:29:27,043
I've lost both my therapist
and my partner.

820
00:29:27,043 --> 00:29:29,020
I'm s...

821
00:29:29,020 --> 00:29:30,023
Th-They died?

822
00:29:30,024 --> 00:29:31,054
No. No, they turned on me.

823
00:29:31,054 --> 00:29:32,064
Some would argue that's worse.

824
00:29:32,064 --> 00:29:34,004
All right, you need to leave.

825
00:29:34,004 --> 00:29:36,047
No, I'm close to something.
I can feel it.

826
00:29:36,048 --> 00:29:38,018
This is not about you!

827
00:29:38,018 --> 00:29:39,051
(groans):
Gah.

828
00:29:41,005 --> 00:29:42,005
You're right.

829
00:29:42,005 --> 00:29:43,035
Yes.

830
00:29:43,035 --> 00:29:45,035
I should use one of you
as a case study.

831
00:29:45,035 --> 00:29:46,052
Thank you for volunteering.

832
00:29:46,052 --> 00:29:48,059
So what...

833
00:29:48,059 --> 00:29:51,032
what makes you jealous? Hmm?

834
00:29:51,032 --> 00:29:55,006
What do you desire
that you can't have?

835
00:29:55,006 --> 00:29:56,009
Come on.

836
00:29:57,013 --> 00:29:58,033
I...

837
00:29:58,033 --> 00:29:59,046
Yeah?

838
00:29:59,047 --> 00:30:01,043
I want Sandy.

839
00:30:03,014 --> 00:30:04,094
What?

840
00:30:04,094 --> 00:30:07,007
Oh.

841
00:30:07,007 --> 00:30:09,057
I remember you now.

842
00:30:09,058 --> 00:30:12,034
Tissue Lad!

843
00:30:12,034 --> 00:30:15,031
Wanted some open relationship
therapy of your own, is that it?

844
00:30:15,031 --> 00:30:17,001
That's not what it is like.

845
00:30:17,002 --> 00:30:18,058
But she didn't want you,
did she?

846
00:30:18,058 --> 00:30:20,052
Sandy loved her husband,

847
00:30:20,052 --> 00:30:23,032
so you killed him, didn't you?

848
00:30:23,032 --> 00:30:24,025
Shut up!

849
00:30:24,026 --> 00:30:25,032
(gasps)
Solved it, haven't I?

850
00:30:25,032 --> 00:30:27,006
Eh?! Haven't I?

851
00:30:27,006 --> 00:30:28,049
(patients clamoring)

852
00:30:28,049 --> 00:30:29,049
So that's a yes.

853
00:30:29,050 --> 00:30:31,013
MAN:
He's got a knife!

854
00:30:31,013 --> 00:30:33,030
Do you realize what you've done?

855
00:30:33,030 --> 00:30:35,030
I had to kill him, all right?

856
00:30:35,030 --> 00:30:37,063
He lied to her.
He cheated on her.

857
00:30:37,064 --> 00:30:40,047
And I tried to tip her off,
but no matter what he did,

858
00:30:40,047 --> 00:30:41,061
she still loved him.

859
00:30:41,061 --> 00:30:42,094
No, no, not that.

860
00:30:42,094 --> 00:30:45,044
This. Right here.

861
00:30:45,044 --> 00:30:47,095
You've just given me the perfect
example of unbridled jealousy.

862
00:30:47,095 --> 00:30:50,028
I'm not jealous. I'm not.

863
00:30:50,028 --> 00:30:52,095
The woman that you loved
was with someone else,

864
00:30:52,095 --> 00:30:55,019
someone you thought
wasn't worthy of her.

865
00:30:55,019 --> 00:30:58,029
But no matter what you did...

866
00:30:58,029 --> 00:31:00,069
she never saw you
the way you wanted her to.

867
00:31:00,069 --> 00:31:03,036
That's...

868
00:31:03,036 --> 00:31:04,096
That's pretty accurate.

869
00:31:04,096 --> 00:31:06,070
Yeah.

870
00:31:06,070 --> 00:31:08,043
You've just made me
realize something.

871
00:31:10,004 --> 00:31:13,044
That my situation
and yours are...

872
00:31:13,044 --> 00:31:16,014
absolutely nothing alike.

873
00:31:16,014 --> 00:31:18,001
I was right! Not jealous!

874
00:31:18,001 --> 00:31:19,044
CHLOE:
Drop your weapon!

875
00:31:19,045 --> 00:31:21,038
(both grunting)

876
00:31:22,028 --> 00:31:24,005
Ow!
Ooh.

877
00:31:26,075 --> 00:31:28,019
(grunts)

878
00:31:28,019 --> 00:31:29,055
Did you seriously

879
00:31:29,056 --> 00:31:31,015
just bite me?

880
00:31:31,016 --> 00:31:32,046
(sighs)

881
00:31:32,046 --> 00:31:33,069
He's the killer.

882
00:31:33,069 --> 00:31:35,009
(panting)

883
00:31:35,009 --> 00:31:37,053
Yeah, you think?

884
00:31:37,053 --> 00:31:39,006
(indistinct
police radio chatter)

885
00:31:48,011 --> 00:31:49,017
(engine starts)

886
00:31:58,008 --> 00:31:59,048
So you were right
about Linda.

887
00:31:59,049 --> 00:32:01,022
She helped me figure
out the motive.

888
00:32:01,022 --> 00:32:04,076
And then I realized Jonathan
and Dr. Shaw's offices

889
00:32:04,076 --> 00:32:06,049
shared the same
security system.

890
00:32:06,049 --> 00:32:07,069
So I checked and...

891
00:32:07,069 --> 00:32:10,009
You're not listening
to me, are you?

892
00:32:12,013 --> 00:32:14,043
Afraid not.

893
00:32:15,067 --> 00:32:17,010
You didn't see any similarity

894
00:32:17,010 --> 00:32:18,070
between yourself and Jonathan?

895
00:32:18,070 --> 00:32:21,047
So you heard some of that,
did you?

896
00:32:21,047 --> 00:32:23,014
Tail end.

897
00:32:23,014 --> 00:32:26,038
(sighs)

898
00:32:26,038 --> 00:32:28,051
I don't know.

899
00:32:28,051 --> 00:32:29,055
Did you?

900
00:32:30,058 --> 00:32:33,042
Mm-mm. No.

901
00:32:33,042 --> 00:32:35,012
Completely different.

902
00:32:35,012 --> 00:32:37,082
That's what I thought.

903
00:32:37,082 --> 00:32:40,049
(chuckles)

904
00:32:40,049 --> 00:32:43,016
So... how's your secret case
with Dan going?

905
00:32:43,016 --> 00:32:44,043
Secretly terrible.

906
00:32:44,043 --> 00:32:45,053
Do you remember Malcolm?

907
00:32:46,057 --> 00:32:47,056
Coma boy?

908
00:32:48,060 --> 00:32:49,080
He woke up.

909
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:51,027
He claims he's innocent.

910
00:32:53,021 --> 00:32:55,081
Something he said bothers me.

911
00:32:55,081 --> 00:32:57,057
Whoever shot him
knew about Palmetto,

912
00:32:57,058 --> 00:33:00,008
but he says that no one
should have known he was there.

913
00:33:00,008 --> 00:33:02,025
Well, you found him there.

914
00:33:02,025 --> 00:33:04,055
Yeah, I...
He pointed that out, too.

915
00:33:04,055 --> 00:33:07,028
So, whoever followed him
could have done what I did.

916
00:33:07,029 --> 00:33:09,009
So how did you track him?

917
00:33:09,009 --> 00:33:11,056
Partners on the force
share GPS locators in their gear

918
00:33:11,056 --> 00:33:13,062
so that they can find each other
in emergencies.

919
00:33:13,063 --> 00:33:16,086
You hacked
his partner's locator.

920
00:33:16,086 --> 00:33:19,010
Which means...

921
00:33:19,010 --> 00:33:21,043
Malcolm's partner knew
he was there, too.

922
00:33:23,030 --> 00:33:24,084
Tony Paolucci knew.

923
00:33:38,072 --> 00:33:40,072
♪ ♪

924
00:33:43,052 --> 00:33:45,052
(knocking)

925
00:33:45,052 --> 00:33:48,043
That's Paolucci's car,
just like his GPS said.

926
00:33:48,043 --> 00:33:49,063
But the bar's closed.

927
00:33:49,063 --> 00:33:52,063
Maybe he decided
to keep the party going.

928
00:33:54,063 --> 00:33:56,020
(door creaks)

929
00:33:57,060 --> 00:33:59,047
(chuckles)

930
00:34:00,077 --> 00:34:02,067
You have to stop doing that.

931
00:34:02,067 --> 00:34:04,037
It was unlocked.

932
00:34:06,051 --> 00:34:09,038
♪ ♪

933
00:34:14,079 --> 00:34:16,092
Paolucci, you in here?

934
00:34:22,016 --> 00:34:24,076
♪ ♪

935
00:34:45,028 --> 00:34:47,048
At least you can see
what he was thinking.

936
00:34:47,049 --> 00:34:49,025
(scoffs)

937
00:34:55,059 --> 00:34:58,036
(indistinct police radio
chatter)

938
00:35:00,040 --> 00:35:02,033
Dan.

939
00:35:05,097 --> 00:35:07,030
(sighs)

940
00:35:07,031 --> 00:35:08,094
I found a suicide note.

941
00:35:09,098 --> 00:35:11,034
In his handwriting?

942
00:35:12,034 --> 00:35:13,078
Sure looks like it.

943
00:35:13,078 --> 00:35:15,075
Apparently, he was on the take.

944
00:35:15,075 --> 00:35:17,098
Malcolm was onto him,
so Paolucci shot him.

945
00:35:17,098 --> 00:35:19,058
When Malcolm woke up,

946
00:35:19,059 --> 00:35:21,035
Paolucci couldn't take
the guilt anymore.

947
00:35:27,086 --> 00:35:29,036
You okay?

948
00:35:30,036 --> 00:35:31,073
Paolucci was an ass,

949
00:35:31,073 --> 00:35:34,083
but this... I can't
imagine this.

950
00:35:34,083 --> 00:35:36,070
I know.

951
00:35:36,070 --> 00:35:38,050
I know.

952
00:35:55,025 --> 00:35:56,039
(knocking)

953
00:35:56,039 --> 00:35:58,066
Uh, come in.

954
00:35:58,066 --> 00:36:00,029
Hello, Doctor.

955
00:36:02,029 --> 00:36:03,066
(sighs)

956
00:36:03,066 --> 00:36:06,013
Thank you for coming.

957
00:36:06,013 --> 00:36:08,060
Uh, I know we're not due
for a session for a few days.

958
00:36:08,060 --> 00:36:10,070
No, my bad.

959
00:36:10,070 --> 00:36:12,080
I realize I'm not up to date
on my payments, so... (chuckles)

960
00:36:14,031 --> 00:36:15,084
Uh...

961
00:36:15,084 --> 00:36:16,094
don't.

962
00:36:19,051 --> 00:36:21,038
What's wrong?
Nothing's wrong.

963
00:36:21,038 --> 00:36:23,005
I realized a few things.

964
00:36:23,005 --> 00:36:25,075
As I said,

965
00:36:25,075 --> 00:36:29,045
we made a breakthrough.

966
00:36:29,045 --> 00:36:33,086
And I think, with that in mind,

967
00:36:33,086 --> 00:36:36,033
we should keep our relationship
professional from now on.

968
00:36:36,033 --> 00:36:37,046
Oh.

969
00:36:37,046 --> 00:36:38,060
Are you sure?

970
00:36:38,060 --> 00:36:40,043
Very much so.

971
00:36:41,083 --> 00:36:43,033
Very well.

972
00:36:43,034 --> 00:36:45,080
If, uh...
if you think it's best.

973
00:36:45,080 --> 00:36:46,080
I do.

974
00:36:46,081 --> 00:36:48,057
Right.

975
00:36:48,057 --> 00:36:52,061
Well, I'll, um... see you
at my next session, then.

976
00:36:58,085 --> 00:36:59,092
(door closes)

977
00:36:59,092 --> 00:37:00,095
(sighs)

978
00:37:00,095 --> 00:37:02,050
(door opens)

979
00:37:02,050 --> 00:37:04,005
One last thing before I go.
Yes?

980
00:37:04,006 --> 00:37:06,079
Dr. Canaan down the hall--
what's he like?

981
00:37:07,083 --> 00:37:09,099
Uh, thoughtful.

982
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:12,006
Spiritual. Why?

983
00:37:12,006 --> 00:37:14,000
Little sanctimonious?

984
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:16,000
I don't know. I suppose.

985
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:18,057
Six-foot-two, black,
voice like an angel?

986
00:37:18,057 --> 00:37:19,077
Oh, you know him.

987
00:37:19,077 --> 00:37:22,044
(sighing)

988
00:37:22,044 --> 00:37:24,061
All too well.

989
00:37:28,095 --> 00:37:30,061
Trixie's finally down.

990
00:37:30,062 --> 00:37:32,092
(chuckles) She conned you
into reading the book

991
00:37:32,092 --> 00:37:34,092
about the sneezing panda,
didn't she?

992
00:37:34,092 --> 00:37:36,062
Five times.

993
00:37:36,062 --> 00:37:38,009
(chuckling)

994
00:37:42,043 --> 00:37:44,089
Hey. Um... (sighs)

995
00:37:44,090 --> 00:37:46,070
thank you.

996
00:37:47,083 --> 00:37:49,040
For what?

997
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:53,060
You know,
for having my back and...

998
00:37:53,061 --> 00:37:54,077
for everything.

999
00:38:03,005 --> 00:38:04,071
You're welcome.

1000
00:38:06,012 --> 00:38:07,038
For everything.

1001
00:38:21,043 --> 00:38:23,060
You should go.

1002
00:38:25,004 --> 00:38:26,067
Yeah, I should.

1003
00:38:26,067 --> 00:38:28,081
I'm sorry.

1004
00:38:28,081 --> 00:38:31,054
No. Don't be sorry.

1005
00:38:32,091 --> 00:38:35,041
(sighs)

1006
00:38:37,092 --> 00:38:39,042
(phone buzzing)

1007
00:38:40,082 --> 00:38:42,082
(groaning sigh)

1008
00:38:47,056 --> 00:38:49,056
(sighs)

1009
00:38:54,010 --> 00:38:57,010
(sighs)

1010
00:38:57,010 --> 00:38:59,004
All right. (chuckles)

1011
00:38:59,004 --> 00:39:00,080
Okay.

1012
00:39:00,081 --> 00:39:02,011
Bye.

1013
00:39:21,083 --> 00:39:23,083
MALCOLM:
Evening, Dan.

1014
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:28,000
I got your text.

1015
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:29,087
What do you want?

1016
00:39:30,090 --> 00:39:32,050
(sighs)

1017
00:39:32,050 --> 00:39:35,024
Just wanted to congratulate you
on closing Palmetto.

1018
00:39:35,024 --> 00:39:37,091
You and that smart,
sexy lady of yours

1019
00:39:37,091 --> 00:39:39,068
caught the guy who shot me.

1020
00:39:42,061 --> 00:39:45,001
That's what
the confession said, right?

1021
00:39:46,022 --> 00:39:49,075
How long did it
take you to write it?

1022
00:39:49,075 --> 00:39:51,009
(laughing)

1023
00:39:51,009 --> 00:39:53,052
Forever.
I mean, I'm so not a word guy.

1024
00:39:53,053 --> 00:39:55,079
(laughing):
You know?

1025
00:39:55,079 --> 00:39:58,053
What? You should be thanking me.

1026
00:39:58,053 --> 00:40:00,026
Why is that?

1027
00:40:00,027 --> 00:40:03,063
Well, I could have told
everyone the truth--

1028
00:40:03,064 --> 00:40:05,084
that you shot me.

1029
00:40:06,087 --> 00:40:08,004
Why didn't you?

1030
00:40:15,088 --> 00:40:17,051
'Cause I like you.

1031
00:40:17,052 --> 00:40:20,098
And I can't imagine what
would happen to your life

1032
00:40:20,099 --> 00:40:23,029
if people found out the truth.

1033
00:40:23,029 --> 00:40:25,019
Your colleagues, your ex...

1034
00:40:25,019 --> 00:40:27,082
I swear to God, I will...
What? Shoot me?

1035
00:40:27,083 --> 00:40:29,066
Ah, been there, done that.

1036
00:40:29,066 --> 00:40:31,076
Big fail. (laughs)

1037
00:40:31,076 --> 00:40:34,073
Besides, you wouldn't
want anything

1038
00:40:34,073 --> 00:40:36,067
to mess
with your pretty little family

1039
00:40:36,067 --> 00:40:38,080
now that you're working
to fix things, right?

1040
00:40:39,094 --> 00:40:41,064
Whatever you want to do to me,

1041
00:40:41,064 --> 00:40:43,007
you keep them out of it.
Dan.

1042
00:40:44,064 --> 00:40:46,031
Come on.

1043
00:40:46,031 --> 00:40:48,008
I'm not gonna hurt anyone.

1044
00:40:49,008 --> 00:40:50,081
No.

1045
00:40:50,082 --> 00:40:52,062
No, no, no, no, no.

1046
00:40:52,062 --> 00:40:54,082
You... you and I...

1047
00:40:56,002 --> 00:40:57,072
...we're gonna be best friends.

1048
00:40:57,072 --> 00:40:59,006
Yeah.

1049
00:40:59,006 --> 00:41:01,076
Because I got big plans for you.

1050
00:41:01,076 --> 00:41:03,013
Big plans.

1051
00:41:03,013 --> 00:41:05,033
(laughing)

1052
00:41:05,033 --> 00:41:07,060
Fun, right?

1053
00:41:07,060 --> 00:41:09,087
We're having fun now.

1054
00:41:09,087 --> 00:41:11,063
(laughs)
(engine starts)

1055
00:41:17,078 --> 00:41:20,064
(dance music playing)

1056
00:41:28,059 --> 00:41:31,022
♪ I've been hell-bent, baby ♪

1057
00:41:31,022 --> 00:41:34,099
♪ Hell-bent on loving you
all day long ♪

1058
00:41:34,099 --> 00:41:39,073
♪ Hell-bent on drugs
'cause they turn you on ♪

1059
00:41:39,073 --> 00:41:42,077
♪ Don't know
what else to do... ♪

1060
00:41:44,087 --> 00:41:47,074
I just learned
the strangest thing.

1061
00:41:47,074 --> 00:41:51,081
Spoiler alert:
Amenadiel found Dr. Linda.

1062
00:41:51,081 --> 00:41:54,091
He was an angel on her shoulder,
trying to control me.

1063
00:41:54,091 --> 00:41:57,031
I wonder how my dear,
angelic brother

1064
00:41:57,032 --> 00:41:59,092
got such a wickedly clever idea.

1065
00:42:02,029 --> 00:42:04,002
I did it to protect you.

1066
00:42:04,002 --> 00:42:05,082
I told you,

1067
00:42:05,082 --> 00:42:08,016
whatever the danger,
I'll be there to stop it.

1068
00:42:08,016 --> 00:42:10,003
Whether you see it
coming or not.

1069
00:42:10,003 --> 00:42:11,076
You betrayed me, Maze.

1070
00:42:12,093 --> 00:42:14,040
And not for my own good.

1071
00:42:14,040 --> 00:42:16,023
You did it for yourself.

1072
00:42:17,094 --> 00:42:21,000
Who is this human world
